#: ../../../guides/faq.md:36
msgid "How to run non-nix executables?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/faq.md:38
msgid ""
"NixOS cannot run dynamically linked executables intended for generic Linux "
"environments out of the box. This is because, by design, it does not have a "
"global library path, nor does it follow the [Filesystem Hierarchy Standard]"
"(https://refspecs.linuxfoundation.org/FHS_3.0/fhs/index.html) (FHS)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/faq.md:41
msgid ""
"There are a few ways to resolve this mismatch in environment expectations:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/faq.md:43
msgid ""
"Use the version packaged in Nixpkgs, if there is one. You can search "
"available packages at <https://search.nixos.org/packages>."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/faq.md:46
msgid ""
"Write a Nix expression for the program to package it in your own "
"configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/faq.md:48
msgid "There are multiple approaches to this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/faq.md:49
msgid "Build from source."
msgstr "從來源碼建置。"

#: ../../../guides/faq.md:51
msgid ""
"Many open-source programs are highly flexible at compile time in terms of "
"where their files go. For an introduction to this, see [](packaging-"
"tutorial)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/faq.md:53
msgid ""
"Modify the program's [ELF header](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Executable_and_Linkable_Format) to include paths to libraries using "
"[`autoPatchelfHook`](https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#setup-hook-"
"autopatchelfhook)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/faq.md:55
msgid "Do this if building from source isn't feasible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/faq.md:56
msgid ""
"Wrap the program to run in an FHS-like environment using [`buildFHSEnv`]"
"(https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#sec-fhs-environments)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/faq.md:58
msgid ""
"This is a last resort, but sometimes necessary, for example if the program "
"downloads and runs other executables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/faq.md:60
msgid ""
"Create a library path that only applies to unpackaged programs by using "
"[`nix-ld`](https://github.com/Mic92/nix-ld). Add this to your `configuration."
"nix`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/faq.md:63
msgid ""
"  programs.nix-ld.enable = true;\n"
"  programs.nix-ld.libraries = with pkgs; [\n"
"    # Add any missing dynamic libraries for unpackaged programs\n"
"    # here, NOT in environment.systemPackages\n"
"  ];\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/faq.md:71
msgid ""
"Then run `nixos-rebuild switch`, and log out and back in again to propagate "
"the new environment variables. (This is only necessary when enabling `nix-"
"ld`; changes in included libraries take effect immediately on rebuild.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/faq.md:75
msgid "`nix-ld` does not work for 32-bit executables on `x86_64` machines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/faq.md:78
msgid ""
"Run your program in the FHS-like environment made for the Steam package "
"using [`steam-run`](https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#sec-steam-run):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/faq.md:80
